2026-07-02 22:57:56,095 Acme Solutions Inc. Employee Handbook & Global Benefits Guide - 2026 1. Welcome to Acme Solutions Welcome to the team! At Acme Solutions, our mission is to deliver seamless, innovative products that improve the daily lives of our customers. We value transparency, continuous learning, and a healthy work-life balance. This document outlines the core policies, benefits, and guidelines that apply to all full-time employees. 2. Paid Time Off (PTO) Policy We believe that taking time off to rest and recharge is essential for long-term success. Acme Solutions offers a tiered PTO system based on an employee's tenure with the company. PTO covers vacations, personal days, and brief illnesses. Important PTO Rule: Any accrued PTO exceeding the "Maximum Rollover" limit at the end of the calendar year (December 31st) will be forfeited. Paid sick leave (up to 7 days annually) is tracked separately and does not roll over . 3. Remote Work and Equipment Stipends Acme Solutions operates on a flexible hybrid model. Employees may choose to work from home up to 3 days a week. To support a productive home environment, the company provides the following financial assistance: Home Office Setup: A one-time stipend of $500 for purchasing ergonomic chairs, desks, or secondary monitors. · Internet Allowance: A monthly reimbursement of $50 to cover high-speed internet costs. · Hardware Upgrades: Laptops are refreshed every 3 years. Employees may request accessories (keyboards, mice, headsets) up to $150 annually. · 4. Health, Wellness, and Retirement We offer comprehensive benefits to ensure the well-being of our team and their families. Health Insurance: Acme covers 90% of the premium for medical, dental, and vision plans for the employee, and 75% for dependents. · 401(k) Matching: The company matches 100% of employee contributions up to 4% of their base salary, and 50% on the next 2%. Contributions vest immediately. · Wellness Subsidy: Employees receive $75 per month that can be used toward gym memberships, yoga classes, or mental health apps like Headspace or Calm. · 5. Code of Conduct and Conflict Resolution"
